tags: i had much more fun drawing doragun XD;
summary: What legendary pokemon do you guys want to meet?
question: What legendary pokemon do you guys want to meet?
answer:
Riku: The Scala Region, like most parts of the Pokemon world, has two legendaries that rule over it. In ancient times, this world was ruled by Light and Darkness of equal parts….But one day, the Denizen of Darkness sought to overcast the Denizen of Light, bringing about a world ruled by strong emotions, hatred, and shadow. This pokemon, now known as Doragun, was eventually thwarted by the efforts of the Denizen of Light, Sparkaga.


However, the effort of sealing away the Denizen of Darkness had exhausted Sparkaga’s powers and she sealed herself behind what we refer to as the “Door to Light”, as she had sealed Doragun behind the “Door to Darkness”. Today, the world exists in a delicate balance of light and darkness, in hopes that the scales don’t tip too far in either direction…

Riku: I admit, I’ve always been more curious about Doragun, and why he tried to take over, but I doubt that we would have the chance to meet either of them, because that would mean the world was being thrown into choas. I’m fine with them remaining just legends.

blog.name: moffittarts
blog.title: Eat Pant
blog.description: I'm an amateur cartoonist and the illustrator for the comic Cy:Bear Punk Comics. I'm an 18 year old teen who loves to draw, watch (and obsess over) movies, loves pipe and theater organs and enjoys stand-up comedy. Also I'm very hyperfixated on 'Animal Crossing: New Leaf,’ ’The Nightmare Before Christmas,' 'The Rocky Horror Picture Show,' and my own characters. The Mayor of Halloween Town, Mr. Resetti and Dr. Shrunk are my top favorite characters, but I absolutely adore my own characters and stories. Talk and send me asks, I love it when that happens. (Boy I sure do love my characters, Animal Crossing, The Nightmare Before Christmas, The Rocky Horror Picture Show, Steam Powered Giraffe, The Love Bug movie series, Captain Underpants, Harry Potter, Inside Out and much more that I can't remember at the moment.) I tag all of my art with “Moffitt.”
